      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2) features the iconic wide-body silhouette and the M96 3.6L flat-six, delivering 315 hp through a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. Mechanical integrity is prioritized: the IMS bearing has been proactively upgraded with a LN Engineering ceramic kit, and the rear main seal remains dry. The Viscous Map-Controlled AWD system ensures exceptional power delivery, further enhanced by a Bilstein B16 coilover suite for optimized damping and roll center geometry. Finished in Arctic Silver, the exterior presents well with minor road-going patina. The cockpit features black leather with light bolster wear consistent with mileage. Recent service includes a comprehensive cooling system overhaul and fresh Michelin Pilot Sport 4S tires mounted on factory 18-inch 'Turbo Twist' alloys. A high-performance, mechanically sorted example ready for spirited driving.",
